vital-Vim-Lua-String
==============================================================================
[![Travis CI](https://img.shields.io/travis/lambdalisue/vital-Vim-Lua-String/master.svg?style=flat-square&label=Travis%20CI)](https://travis-ci.org/lambdalisue/vital-Vim-Lua-String)
[![AppVeyor](https://img.shields.io/appveyor/ci/lambdalisue/vital-Vim-Lua-String/master.svg?style=flat-square&label=AppVeyor)](https://ci.appveyor.com/project/lambdalisue/vital-Vim-Lua-String/branch/master)
![Version 0.1.0](https://img.shields.io/badge/version-0.1.0-yellow.svg?style=flat-square)
![Support Vim 7.4.2137 or above](https://img.shields.io/badge/support-Vim%207.4.2137%20or%20above-yellowgreen.svg?style=flat-square)
[![MIT License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue.svg?style=flat-square)](LICENSE)
[![Doc](https://img.shields.io/badge/doc-%3Ah%20Vital.Vim.Lua.String-orange.svg?style=flat-square)](doc/vital-vim-lua-string.txt)

Expose native `strwidth()` and `strchars()` by https://github.com/starwing/luautf8 in lua context.
It fallback to use Vim's `strwidth()` and `strchars()` if luautf8 is not available.
